719955f-a.title: Manhattan: Fulton Street - Dutch Street
719955f-a.text:
Fulton Street, north aide, west from (No. 119) the head of Dutch
(left) to Church Streets, and showing at the latter point the Vestry
Office of Trinity Church. The 6-story structure under renovation. is
the Raymond Building, No. 129 Fulton, 98-102 Nassau and 4O Ann Streets.
This view shows it at the N.E. corner of Fulton and Nassau Streets.
Opposing same is the 10-story Bennett Building, on the west side of Nassau,
north from Fulton to Ann Streets.
June 3, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
